Back to Fibonacci
Do you remember the Fibonacci numbers? Here was a naive implementation in R:

fib &lt;- function(n) {
  if(n == 0) return(0)
  if(n == 1) return(1)
  Recall(n - 1) + Recall(n - 2)
}

This function gives the nth number in the sequence.

Example:


fib(30)

[1] 832040

Conditionals
Conditionals determine which section of code is to be ran based on predicates. A predicate is a test that returns either TRUE or FALSE.
Here is an example:

test_sign &lt;- function(x) {
  if (x &gt; 0) {
    "x is positif"
  } else if (x &lt; 0) {
    "x is negatif"
  } else {
    "x is equal to zero"
  }
}

test_sign() is a function that accepts one argument. Depending on the value of that argument, one of three snippets of code is executed:

test_sign(3)

[1] "x is positif"

test_sign(-2)

[1] "x is negatif"

test_sign(0)

[1] "x is equal to zero"

Syntax
Here is the syntax to define a new function:
name &lt;- function(arguments) {
  body
}

What is returned by a function?
In R, the result of the last statement is printed automatically:

test &lt;- function(x, y) {
  x
  y
}
test(2, 3)

[1] 3


If you want to also print other results, you need to explicitly use the print() function:

test &lt;- function(x, y) {
  print(x)
  y
}
test(2, 3)

[1] 2


[1] 3


Note that, unlike print(), the function return() exits the function:

test &lt;- function(x, y) {
  return(x)
  y
}
test(2, 3)

[1] 2



test &lt;- function(x, y) {
  return(x)
  return(y)
}
test(2, 3)

[1] 2

HTML and CSS
HyperText Markup Language (HTML) is the standard markup language for websites: it encodes the information related to the formatting and structure of webpages. Additionally, some of the customization can be stored in Cascading Style Sheets (CSS) files.
HTML uses tags of the form:
&lt;some_tag&gt;Your content&lt;/some_tag&gt;
Some tags have attributes:
&lt;some_tag attribute_name="attribute value"&gt;Your content&lt;/some_tag&gt;

Examples:

Site structure:

&lt;h2&gt;This is a heading of level 2&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a paragraph&lt;/p&gt;

Formatting:

&lt;b&gt;This is bold&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;a href="https://some.url"&gt;This is the text for a link&lt;/a&gt;

